    "author_association": "NONE",
    "body": "### Problem\r\n\r\nThe cursor blinks rapidly, sometimes not allowing me to execute commands or open files.\r\n\r\n```vimscript\r\nlet g:netrw_list_hide = '^\\./$,^\\.\\./$'\r\n```\r\n\r\nhttps://github.com/user-attachments/assets/0c846a24-ec7f-4c6b-9ecf-298f3fbfbe9a\r\n\r\n### Steps to reproduce\r\n\r\nOpen Neovim -> execute `:let g:netrw_list_hide = '.'` and `:let g:netrw_hide = 1`\r\n\r\n(You might have to press a key for it to start freaking out like this)\r\n\r\n### Expected behavior\r\n\r\nNetrw Directory Listing *doesn't* do that :)\r\n\r\n### Nvim version (nvim -v)\r\n\r\nNVIM v0.11.0-dev-69553f7-dirty\r\n\r\n### Vim (not Nvim) behaves the same?\r\n\r\nno, Vim 9.1\r\n\r\n### Operating system/version\r\n\r\nFedora Linux Workstation 40\r\n\r\n### Terminal name/version\r\n\r\nGNOME terminal | Version 3.50.1 for GNOME 45\r\n\r\n### $TERM environment variable\r\n\r\nxterm-256color\r\n\r\n### Installation\r\n\r\ndnf install, then built from source while trying to fix myself",
